===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In the {{w|bronze inscriptions}}, an {{Han compound|眉|頁|止|舟|ls=ic|nocap=y|t2=person with prominent head|t3=foot|t4=shoe or (shoe-shaped) boat}}. Possibly {{och-l|履}} is also {{liushu|psc|nocap=1|adj=1}} with phonetic component {{och-l|眉}}.

According to ''{{w|Shuowen}}'', {{Han compound|尸|彳|夊|舟|ls=ic|nocap=y|t2=road|t3=foot|t4=(shoe-shaped) boat}}. Possibly {{liushu|psc|nocap=1|adj=1}}, with {{och-l|尸}} functioning as a phonetic component corrupted from {{och-l|眉}}. Comparing Qin bamboo slip script, ''Shuowen'' seal's {{zh-l|*舟}} was corrupted from {{zh-l|*自}}, and Qin's 自 was simplified from {{zh-l|*頁}}.

Modern form is a compound of {{Han compound|尸|復|t2=return}}.

